            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EYou%20know%20you%20are%20in%20trouble%20when%20you%20feel%20so%20far%20away%20from%20God's%20presence%20that%20your%20address%20might%20as%20well%20be%20%22the%20ends%20of%20the%20earth%22!%20David%20felt%20the%20quicksand%20of%20doubt%2C%20fear%2C%20and%20unbelief%20underneath%20his%20feet.%20As%20he%20grew%20weaker%20by%20the%20minute%2C%20his%20desperate%20cry%20was%20to%20be%20brought%20to%20a%20spiritual%20position%20where%20his%20feet%20could%20feel%20the%20Rock%20of%20God%20beneath%20him.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20moment%20your%20heart%20is%20safely%20settled%20on%20that%20Rock%2C%20God%20will%20keep%20you%20in%20%22perfect%20peace%22%20because%20your%20%22thoughts%20are%20fixed%20on%20%5BHim%5D%22%20(Isaiah%2026%3A3).%20Trust%20is%20the%20feeling%20of%20security%20you%20have%20when%20your%20feet%20are%20solidly%20planted%20on%20a%20Rock%20that%20towers%20high%20above%20all%20your%20enemies.%20%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThat%20Rock%20is%20also%20a%20place%20of%20safety%20where%20you%20can%20find%20secure%20refuge%20and%20shelter%20(Psalm%2061%3A3-4).%20As%20Isaiah%20phrased%20it%2C%20%22But%20to%20the%20poor%2C%20O%20Lord%2C%20you%20are%20a%20refuge%20from%20the%20storm.%20To%20the%20needy%20in%20distress%2C%20you%20are%20a%20shelter%20from%20the%20rain%20and%20heat.%20.%20..%22%20(Isaiah%2025%3A4).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EClimb%20up%20on%20the%20Rock%20right%20now%2C%20and%20rest%20in%20His%20perfect%20peace.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
